Define the callback behaviour for handling bidirectional WebSocket events.

## Context
Callback behaviour defines the contract for event handlers. Must pass tests from T005.

## File to Create
`apps/parrot_media/lib/parrot_media/ws_bidirectional/callback.ex`

## Implementation (from contracts/callback.ex)
```elixir
defmodule ParrotMedia.WsBidirectional.Callback do
  @moduledoc """
  Behaviour for handling bidirectional WebSocket connection events.

  ## Example
      defmodule MyApp.AIHandler do
        @behaviour ParrotMedia.WsBidirectional.Callback

        @impl true
        def handle_event({:connected}, state), do: {:ok, state}
        def handle_event({:ws_message, data}, state), do: {:ok, state}
        def handle_event(_event, state), do: {:ok, state}
      end
  """

  @type event ::
          {:connected}
          | {:disconnected, reason :: term()}
          | {:reconnecting, attempt :: pos_integer()}
          | {:failed, reason :: term()}
          | {:ws_message, data :: binary() | String.t()}
          | {:frames_dropped, count :: pos_integer()}

  @type state :: term()

  @callback handle_event(event(), state()) :: {:ok, state()} | {:error, term()}

  @callback terminate(reason :: term(), state()) :: term()

  @optional_callbacks [terminate: 2]
end
```

