## Behaviour Definition
```elixir
defmodule ParrotSip.CDR.Handler do
  @moduledoc """
  Behaviour for CDR handlers.
  """

  @callback init(args :: term()) :: {:ok, state :: term()} | {:error, reason :: term()}
  @callback handle_cdr(cdr :: ParrotSip.CDR.t(), state :: term()) :: :ok | {:error, term()}

  @optional_callbacks [init: 1]

  def init(args), do: {:ok, args}
end
```

## Design
- init/1 is optional (default passes args through)
- handle_cdr/2 is required
- Return values for logging only (fire-and-forget)

